'''Shigeoka Kawahito''' (滋岳川人) was a {{ill|Heian period|ja|平安時代|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Heian period|qq=}} aristocrat and {{ill|Onmyōji|ja|陰陽師|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Onmyōji|qq=}}. His family name transitioned from {{ill|Togi no Ason|ja|刀岐直|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Togi no Ason|qq=}} to {{ill|Shigeoka no Ason|ja|滋岳朝臣|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shigeoka no Ason|qq=}}. His court Rank reached {{ill|Senior Fifth Rank, Upper Grade|ja|従五位上|1=Junior Fifth Rank|lt=Junior Fifth Rank, Upper Grade|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Senior Fifth Rank, Upper Grade|13=User:Immanuelle/Junior Fifth Rank|qq=}}, and he served as the {{ill|Head of the Bureau of Onmyō|ja|陰陽頭|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Head of the Bureau of Onmyō|qq=}}.

== Lineage ==
The origins of the Togi clan (刀岐氏) are unclear, but they are thought to be descended from the {{ill|Mikata District|ja|美方郡|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Mikata District|qq=}} Togi area in {{ill|Tajima Province|ja|但馬国|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tajima Province|qq=}} (modern {{ill|Shin'onsen Town|ja|新温泉町|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shin'onsen Town|qq=}}, {{ill|Hyōgo Prefecture|ja|兵庫県|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hyōgo Prefecture|qq=}}){{sfn|Ōta|1963|loc=3908}}. As a clan with the "Na" surname (直), they may have also been part of the {{ill|Mikata Province Governors|ja|二方国造|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Mikata Province Governors|qq=}} lineage.

== Career ==
In {{ill|Ninju 4|ja|仁寿4年|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ninju 4|qq=}} ({{ill|854|ja|854年|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/854|qq=}}), Kawahito and his relatives, including Togi no Masaru (then serving as {{ill|Kazusa Province|ja|上総国|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kazusa Province|qq=}} Provincial Secretary), were granted the surname {{ill|Shigeoka no Ason|ja|滋岳朝臣|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shigeoka no Ason|qq=}}. At the time, he held the Rank {{ill|Senior Sixth Rank, Upper Grade|ja|正六位上|1=Senior Sixth Rank|lt=Senior Sixth Rank, Upper Grade|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Senior Sixth Rank, Upper Grade|13=User:Immanuelle/Senior Sixth Rank|qq=}} and the positions {{ill|Junior Assistant of the Bureau of Onmyō|ja|陰陽権允|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Junior Assistant of the Bureau of Onmyō|qq=}} and {{ill|Onmyō Hakase|ja|陰陽博士|1=Onmyō Hakase|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Onmyō Hakase|13=User:Immanuelle/Onmyō Hakase|qq=}}. Kawahito continued to serve as an Onmyō Doctor for more than 20 years, spanning the reigns of {{ill|Emperor Montoku|ja|文徳天皇|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Emperor Montoku|qq=}} and {{ill|Emperor Seiwa|ja|Emperor Seiwa|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Emperor Seiwa|qq=}}, eventually ascending to {{ill|Head of the Bureau of Onmyō|ja|陰陽頭|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Head of the Bureau of Onmyō|qq=}}. As an Onmyōji, his activities are well documented:
- In {{ill|Tian'an 2|ja|天安2nd year|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tian'an 2|qq=}} ({{ill|858|ja|858年|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/858|qq=}}), Kawahito, along with {{ill|Abe no Asomi|ja|安倍安仁|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Abe no Asomi|qq=}} and others, selected a burial site for {{ill|Emperor Montoku|ja|文徳天皇|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Emperor Montoku|qq=}} in the {{ill|Katsuno District|ja|葛野郡|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Katsuno District|qq=}}, {{ill|Yamashiro Province|ja|Yamashiro Province|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yamashiro Province|qq=}}.<ref>『{{ill|Nihon Sandai Jitsuroku|ja|日本三代実録|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nihon Sandai Jitsuroku|qq=}}』天安2nd year 9月2日条</ref>
- In {{ill|Jōgan 1|ja|貞観元年|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Jōgan 1|qq=}} ({{ill|859|ja|859年|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/859|qq=}}), he and {{ill|Fujihara no Yamakage|ja|藤原山蔭|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Fujihara no Yamakage|qq=}} performed a ritual in {{ill|Yoshino District|ja|吉野郡|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yoshino District|qq=}}, {{ill|Yamato Province|ja|大和国|qq=Yamato Province|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yamato Province|qq=}} to prevent pestilence.<ref>『{{ill|Nihon Sandai Jitsuroku|ja|日本三代実録|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nihon Sandai Jitsuroku|qq=}}』貞観元年8月3日条</ref>
- In {{ill|Jōgan 5|ja|貞観5年|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Jōgan 5|qq=}} ({{ill|863|ja|863年|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/863|qq=}}), he conducted further rituals to address similar concerns.<ref>『日本三代実録』貞観5th year 2月1日条</ref>
Kawahito's activities significantly influenced the rituals and practices during this period, particularly in the establishment of the {{ill|Takamayama Festival|ja|高山祭|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Takamayama Festival|qq=}}.

== Works and Legacy ==
Kawahito is credited with foundational works in Japanese {{ill|Onmyōdō|ja|陰陽道|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Onmyōdō|qq=}}, including 『{{ill|Seiyō Dōsei-kyō|ja|世要動静経|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Seiyō Dōsei-kyō|qq=}}』 and 『{{ill|Kinshū Shinjutsu Tonkō-sho|ja|滋川新術遁甲書|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kinshū Shinjutsu Tonkō-sho|qq=}}』.<ref>{{ill|Nihon Sandai Jitsuroku|ja|日本三代実録|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nihon Sandai Jitsuroku|qq=}}貞観16年5月27日条</ref> Although these are lost, they heavily influenced subsequent practitioners and texts.

== Timeline of Ranks ==
* {{ill|Ninju 4|ja|仁寿4年|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ninju 4|qq=}}: Promoted to {{ill|Senior Fifth Rank|ja|従五位下|1=Junior Fifth Rank|lt=Junior Fifth Rank, Lower Grade|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Senior Fifth Rank|13=User:Immanuelle/Junior Fifth Rank|qq=}}
* {{ill|Jōgan 3|ja|貞観3年|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Jōgan 3|qq=}}: Appointed {{ill|Assistant Governor of Harima Province|ja|播磨権大掾|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Assistant Governor of Harima Province|qq=}}

