The origins of the Togi clan (刀岐氏) are unclear, but they are thought to be descended from the [[:en:Mikata District, Hyōgo|Mikata District]] Togi area in [[:en:Tajima Province|Tajima Province]] (modern [[:en:Shin'onsen, Hyōgo|Shin'onsen Town]], [[:en:Hyōgo Prefecture|Hyōgo Prefecture]]){{sfn|Ōta|1963|loc=3908}}. As a clan with the "Na" surname (直), they may have also been part of the {{ill|Mikata Province Governors|ja|二方国造|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Mikata Province Governors|qq=}} lineage.

== Career ==
In {{ill|Ninju 4|ja|仁寿4年|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ninju 4|qq=}} ([[:en:854|854]]), Kawahito and his relatives, including Togi no Masaru (then serving as [[:en:Kazusa Province|Kazusa Province]] Provincial Secretary), were granted the surname {{ill|Shigeoka no Ason|ja|滋岳朝臣|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shigeoka no Ason|qq=}}. At the time, he held the Rank {{ill|Senior Sixth Rank, Upper Grade|ja|正六位上|1=Senior Sixth Rank|lt=Senior Sixth Rank, Upper Grade|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Senior Sixth Rank, Upper Grade|13=User:Immanuelle/Senior Sixth Rank|qq=}} and the positions {{ill|Junior Assistant of the Bureau of Onmyō|ja|陰陽権允|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Junior Assistant of the Bureau of Onmyō|qq=}} and {{ill|Onmyō Hakase|ja|陰陽博士|1=Onmyō Hakase|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Onmyō Hakase|13=User:Immanuelle/Onmyō Hakase|qq=}}. Kawahito continued to serve as an Onmyō Doctor for more than 20 years, spanning the reigns of [[:en:Emperor Montoku|Emperor Montoku]] and {{ill|Emperor Seiwa|ja|Emperor Seiwa|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Emperor Seiwa|qq=}}, eventually ascending to {{ill|Head of the Bureau of Onmyō|ja|陰陽頭|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Head of the Bureau of Onmyō|qq=}}. As an Onmyōji, his activities are well documented:
- In {{ill|Tian'an 2|ja|天安2年|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tian'an 2|qq=}} ([[:en:858|858]]), Kawahito, along with {{ill|Abe no Asomi|ja|安倍安仁|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Abe no Asomi|qq=}} and others, selected a burial site for [[:en:Emperor Montoku|Emperor Montoku]] in the {{ill|Katsuno District|ja|葛野郡|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Katsuno District|qq=}}, {{ill|Yamashiro Province|ja|Yamashiro Province|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yamashiro Province|qq=}}.<ref>『[[:en:Nihon Sandai Jitsuroku|Nihon Sandai Jitsuroku]]』天安2nd year 9月2日条</ref>
- In {{ill|Jōgan 1|ja|貞観元年|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Jōgan 1|qq=}} ([[:en:859|859]]), he and {{ill|Fujihara no Yamakage|ja|藤原山蔭|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Fujihara no Yamakage|qq=}} performed a ritual in [[:en:Yoshino District, Nara|Yoshino District]], [[:en:Yamato Province|Yamato Province]] to prevent pestilence.<ref>『[[:en:Nihon Sandai Jitsuroku|Nihon Sandai Jitsuroku]]』貞観元年8月3日条</ref>
- In {{ill|Jōgan 5|ja|貞観5年|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Jōgan 5|qq=}} ([[:en:863|863]]), he conducted further rituals to address similar concerns.<ref>『日本三代実録』貞観5th year 2月1日条</ref>
Kawahito's activities significantly influenced the rituals and practices during this period, particularly in the establishment of the [[:en:Takayama Festival|Takamayama Festival]].

== Works and Legacy ==
Kawahito is credited with foundational works in Japanese [[:en:Onmyōdō|Onmyōdō]], including 『{{ill|Seiyō Dōsei-kyō|ja|世要動静経|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Seiyō Dōsei-kyō|qq=}}』 and 『{{ill|Kinshū Shinjutsu Tonkō-sho|ja|滋川新術遁甲書|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kinshū Shinjutsu Tonkō-sho|qq=}}』.<ref>[[:en:Nihon Sandai Jitsuroku|Nihon Sandai Jitsuroku]]貞観16年5月27日条</ref> Although these are lost, they heavily influenced subsequent practitioners and texts.

== Timeline of Ranks ==
* {{ill|Ninju 4|ja|仁寿4年|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ninju 4|qq=}}: Promoted to {{ill|Senior Fifth Rank|ja|従五位下|1=Junior Fifth Rank|lt=Junior Fifth Rank, Lower Grade|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Senior Fifth Rank|13=User:Immanuelle/Junior Fifth Rank|qq=}}
* {{ill|Jōgan 3|ja|貞観3年|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Jōgan 3|qq=}}: Appointed {{ill|Assistant Governor of Harima Province|ja|播磨権大掾|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Assistant Governor of Harima Province|qq=}}

